    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"387244\">Yaël Dillies</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Effros.20Theorem/near/562732022\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>gcongr</code> is relatively new at the scale of mathlib, so there are many missing annotations. Please PR the ones you see are missing! and swapping assumptions to make a lemma eligible for <code>gcongr</code> is definitely fair game.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>My first PR <span aria-label=\"tada\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f389\" role=\"img\" title=\"tada\">:tada:</span> : <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/32686#issuecomment-3636813523\">refactor: add gcongr tag to IsMeagre.mono</a></p>\n<p>I assume switching assumptions will break some things. I am now waiting for the CI tests to tell me what I broke so I can try and fix it.</p>",
